Defendant Jose Luis Rosado-Otero appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Heather L. Johnson appeared by video for Jose Luis Rosado-Otero.  Attorney James C Griffin in court for State of Wisconsin. 
Sworn as interpreter: Patrick Ryan.

Case in court for a plea and sentencing.  Defense requests an adjournment.  Court scheduled the matter as requested.  Case adjourned to Branch 2, Rm 635 CH.
Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for November 11, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Attorney Heather L. Johnson in court, defendant Jose Luis Rosado-Otero not in court, in custody.  James C Griffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
OFF THE RECORD. Case scheduled for plea hearing. Defense requests an adjourned date. Case adjourned, Branch 2.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for September 1, 2022 at 03:30 pm.

Attorney Heather L. Johnson in court, defendant Jose Luis Rosado-Otero not in court, in custody.  James C Griffin appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Hearing held via Zoom. Defense requests a projected guilty plea  date. Case adjourned, Branch 2 room G55 CJF.  Plea hearing scheduled for June 23, 2022 at 02:00 pm.

Defendant Jose Luis Rosado-Otero in court with Attorney Heather L. Johnson; both appear by video.  Defendant Jose Luis Rosado-Otero in custody.  Anna Marie Meulbroek appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case set for a Preliminary Hearing. Parties are advised that this case is assigned to Branch 02, Judge Childs. Defendant waived Preliminary Hearing. Preliminary Hearing Questionnaire and Waiver received and filed. Court held colloquy with defendant. Probable cause has been found and the defendant is bound over for trial. Original Information e-filed, copy given to defense counsel who waived reading. Defense enters a plea of not guilty on behalf of the defendant. Case is adjourned to Br. 02.  Scheduling conference scheduled for April 28, 2022 at 01:30 pm.

Court ordered no contact with In and Out Foods and all employees; Starlite Beer and Food and all employees; AA; DK
No Contact/No Weapons Order, signed and filed.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Jose Luis Rosado-Otero in court with attorney Katherine Graber.  Defendant Jose Luis Rosado-Otero in custody.  Anthony White appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Jose Luis Rosado-Otero appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Childs, Branch 02.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Commissioner advised DNA sample has been obtained from the Defendant.  Court advised Defendant he may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if he meets the conditions under Wisconsin Statutes Section 165.77(4).  This hearing will be streamed live on Dacast:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/99073afd-37c2-acfa-830d-b1ddcaebf0ea  Preliminary hearing scheduled for March 9, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
